</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HKN-BRUINS-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BRUINS GETTING HEALTHY DOSE OF SUCCESS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By NANCY L. MARRAPESE  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   BOSTON _ The Bruins are unbeaten in their last four games
(3-0-1). That run has helped them in their playoff race with
Florida (tied with Boston but with three fewer wins and one more
game played), Montreal, and the Rangers.
</P>
<P>
   Washington, which the Bruins dispatched, 4-3, Saturday, is now 5
points behind Boston for the eighth spot.
</P>
<P>
   As badly as the Bruins have been hit by injuries (145 man
games), things have been even worse for the Capitals (343).
</P>
<P>
   In Boston's case, coach Pat Burns said a key to the team's
recent success has been its return to good health.
</P>
<P>
   ``The whole year it's been like that and now all of a sudden
they're starting to come back and things are starting to settle
down a little bit more,'' said Burns.
</P>
<P>
   Burns acknowledges every game now is crucial and it has helped
the Bruins' cause that they're beating teams in their own
conference.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's very important, every point you get from now until the
end of the year no matter who you beat is going to be important
with the situation that we're in,'' said Burns. ``I've said that
for the last week, we're going to have to take a run at every
single game. If we do that, we have a chance. We're not going to
win every single one but we're going to have to win more than our
share if we expect to get in.''
</P>
<P>
   Before their recent success, the Bruins were mired in a 2-9-2
stretch and appeared to be headed home for the playoffs. Now, they
are distancing themselves from some of the competition.
</P>
<P>
   ``You want to put people behind you and keep putting them behind
you and that way you can look ahead instead of thinking, `Oh, no,
here they come,' '' said Steve Heinze. ``You start beating them and
stop looking in the rear-view mirror and instead you're looking
ahead to catch teams.''
</P>
<P>
   What has revved up the Bruins' offense is the play of the new
top line _ Jason Allison, Dmitri Khristich, and Anson Carter.
Carter has brought a new look in place of Sergei Samsonov, who was
given spot duty Saturday after missing two games with a sinus
infection.
</P>
<P>
   ``Sergei has great speed and is a great one-on-one player,''
said Allison. ``He can dangle. Anson has good speed too but he's
more of a stronger player down low and he can really come up with
those loose pucks and he has a great shot.''
</P>
<P>
   That combination has provided a much-needed jolt to the power
play (3 for 5 Saturday). Even more impressive was Byron Dafoe, who
had 33 saves, several in the final minute.
</P>
<P>
   ``Obviously, we've got to get points every night,'' said Dafoe.
``(Washington) is a team that's vying for that eighth spot and it
was a chance for us to put them behind us a little bit as well as
gain ground on Florida.
</P>
<P>
   ``Every game we have to treat like it's our last one because it
seems like every night we are playing for that eighth spot. Every
game is a playoff game. People might have thought we did better
than most people thought we would last year but our expectations
are a lot higher this year and missing the playoffs is definitely
not in the program. I definitely think we're going to be there at
the end of the season.''
</P>
<P>
   Now that their confidence is back and they're healthy, the
Bruins are looking ahead rather than obsessing over who is on their
tails.
</P>
<P>
   ``When you're playing teams and you see them starting to rise
and get closer to you, you want to keep them down as much as
possible,'' said Tim Taylor. ``The more teams below you, the better
chance you have of getting up to the seventh or sixth seeds. We put
ourselves in this situation 10 games ago by not playing real well.
Now we're starting to play better. We can't really worry about
anyone else, we have to worry about ourselves.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-03-01-99 0229EST &QL; 
