<HEADLINE>
`TOM AND JERRY' SHOWS SHORTS SHOULD STAY SHORT 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``Tom and Jerry: The Movie'' _ When Jack Nicholson
first went to Hollywood, he worked for MGM animators Bill Hanna and
Joe Barbera. He delivered coffee and also answered some ``Tom and
Jerry'' fan mail. That said, this movie points up the value of
brevity. The cartoon cat-and-mouse games were designed as short
subjects, and that's the best way to see them. The feature is too
long.
</P>
<P>
   ``Point of Order'' _ This remarkable documentary focuses on
Senator Joseph McCarthy's rabid assault on the Army. Unlike his
rapacious move to drive fairly defenseless victims of the Red Scare
out of Hollywood, the Wisconsin senator got all he could handle
from the power of the Army. These 1954 congressional hearings make
the recent embarrassments in Washington seem tame.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   MARVELOUS: Marvel Comics superheroes _ Captain America, the
Incredible Hulk, Iron Man, Mighty Thor, Sub-Mariner, and Spider-Man
_ just hit video stores with several episodes from the original
animated TV series. Priced at $14.98 per volume, the series also
includes interviews with creator Stan Lee. The technical qualities
are deficient, with imagery that seems as motionless as the comics
they came from, but the stories are strong.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: March 9: ``What Dreams May Come,'' ``Dead
Man on Campus,'' ``Black Dog,'' ``Slam,'' ``Somebody Is Waiting.''
March 16: ``The Waterboy,'' ``Bulworth,'' ``No Laughing Matter,''
``Living Out Loud,'' ``One True Thing,'' ``Polish Wedding,'' ``Paul
Monette: The Brink of Summer's End,'' ``The Wonderful Ice Cream
Suit,'' ``Who the Hell Is Juliette?'' March 23: ``Pleasantville,''
``Mighty Joe Young,'' ``Firelight,'' ``Bride of Chucky,'' ``Jerry
Springer's Ringmaster,'' ``Carla's Song,'' ``From Dusk Till Dawn
2,'' ``Strike!'' March 30: ``The Rugrats Movie,'' ``Oblomov,''
``Siberiade,'' ``Home Fries,'' ``Mutual Needs.'' April 6:
``Beloved,'' ``American History X,'' ``A Soldier's Daughter Never
Cries,'' ``I Still Know What You Did Last Summer,'' ``An Unexpected
Life,'' ``Meet Joe Black,'' ``The Dentist 2.'' April 13: ``The
Tempest,'' ``Bug Buster,'' ``Ambushed,'' ``Basil,'' ``Detroit
9000,'' ``Conspirators of Pleasure.'' April 20: ``A Bug's Life,''
``Monument Ave.,'' ``Simon Birch,'' ``Apt Pupil,'' ``A Night at the
Roxbury.'' April 27: ``Happiness,'' ``Ground Control.'' May 4:
``Babe: Pig in the City.'' May 11: ``Another Day in Paradise.''
</P>
</TEXT>
