 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 
March 1, 1999 JASPER-TRIAL (Jasper, Texas) _ Editors: For those who used the
JASPER-TRIAL stories that were sent to the wires Wednesday, Feb.
24, and Friday, Feb. 26, the stories contained an error. In those
stories about the capital murder trial of John William ``Bill''
King in Jasper, the Houston Chronicle incorrectly reported that
King was the first white man convicted of killing a black person in
Texas in modern times. However, Donald Vigneault, who is white, was
sentenced to death in the 1979 Matagorda County slaying of Loretta
Jones, a black woman. Although Vigneault spent several years on
death row, his name escaped prison records because he died of
natural causes in 1997. 
 
c.1999 Houston Chronicle 
 
 
