   OLYMPICS
</P>
<P>
   OLY-IOC-EXPULSIONS _ LAUSANNE, Switzerland _ IOC completes
private meetings on expulsion of some members; today is deadline
for bid cities (including Atlanta) to submit reports. (Roughton,
Cox News Service and Turner, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in the (s) sports and (i) international categories.
</P>
<P>
   OLY-IOC-ATLANTA _ ACOG releases details of its letter to the IOC
on a lack of abuses by IOC members during the bid for the 1996
Games. (Turner, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in the (s) sports and (a) general news categories.
</P>
<P>
   OLY-USOC-SALTLAKE _ The USOC releases its investigative report
on Salt Lake, which is expected to recommend changes on how
American bid cities are selected. The IOC's role in the scandal and
its cleanup is likely to be a focus of the Mitchell report. (Rosen,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in the (s) sports and (a) general news categories.
</P>
<P>
   BASKETBALL
</P>
<P>
   COLLEGES
</P>
<P>
   BKC-NCAA-BUBBLE _ The NCAA tournament field will be announced
Sunday and for the first time since the field expanded to 64, there
is talk that the ACC will get only three teams. Duke, Maryland and
North Carolina are the only locks from a conference that annually
places five to six teams in the NCAA tournament. The SEC, on the
other hand, appears to have five teams worthy of NCAA bids, with
two more on the bubble entering this week's conference tournament
at the Georgia Dome. (Barnhart, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   BKC-SEC-TOURNEY _ The Southeastern Conference and the Georgia
Dome have shared a successful partnership with the postseason
basketball tournament in the past, and both parties are looking
forward to this year's event beginning Thursday afternoon. The two
SEC tournament championship games with the highest attendance were
held at the Georgia Dome and officials hope this year's event
surpasses the attendance record set in 1995. Meanwhile, league
players and coaches enjoy playing at the Dome including Kentucky,
which has won all of its 10 career games at the facility. (Towers,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   SOCCER
</P>
<P>
   INTSOCCER-NOTES _ International soccer notes column. (Parker,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
