   &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   A Boston Globe article about municipal elections in Tehran
incorrectly identified Mahsan Kadivar, a clerical leader in the
reform movement, as a candidate for the Tehran city council.
Kadivar's sister, Jamileh Kadivar, was the candidate and was among
the leading vote getters in the election. She ran for the seat
after Mahsan Kadivar was disqualified by conservative opponents as
a candidate in elections last year for national seats on the
religious Council of Experts.
</P>
