<P>
   HUMBLE-KILLER &QL;
</P>
<P>
   OLNEY, Texas _ When Faryion Wardrip showed up in Olney a year
ago wearing an electronic monitoring device on his ankle, residents
didn't ask any questions. They took him at his word when he said he
had been paroled after he was convicted of accidentally killing a
woman in an automobile accident and had paid his debt to society.
What Wardrip didn't tell folks in this town 93 miles northwest of
Fort Worth was that he had been convicted of murder. And two weeks
ago, police said he has admitted killing three other women _
including one in Fort Worth _ more than a decade ago. By BILL
HANNA. Story has moved in ``a'' general news category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   P O L I T I C A L &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
