enough, ``Juneteenth,'' the second and last novel we will ever get
from Ralph Ellison. Because Ellison's masterwork ``Invisible Man''
was published in 1952, and because his second novel has been
anticipated since he began working on it in 1954, it seems almost
cruel that the publisher will make us wait any longer for
``Juneteenth.'' By JEFF GUINN. Story has moved in ``e''
entertainment category. &QL; 
