<HEADLINE>
TOURISTS KIDNAPPED IN UGANDA 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (ATTN: Great Britain)  (mk) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NAIROBI, Kenya _ Thirteen foreign tourists and an unknown number
of Ugandans were kidnapped early Monday morning while tracking
mountain gorillas in a forest near Uganda's southwestern border.
</P>
<P>
   Three of the tourists were Americans, said Virgil Bodeen, a
spokesman for the American Embassy. Officials said several of the
others were British. The kidnappers appeared to be Rwandans.
</P>
</TEXT>
