<P>
   MARKET (New York) _ Fresh signs of strong economic growth preyed
on the bond market again, pulling down stock prices early, but
major market gauges pared their declines and closed narrowly mixed
on unusually light volume. By Kenneth N. Gilpin.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 8:30 p.m. ET.)
</P>
<P>
   (Top display)
</P>
<P>
   GUCCI-LVMH (Undated) _ As the fashion set gathers in Europe this
week to preview fall collections, cashmere sweatshirts and fur
