cover preserves near Anganueo, Mexico, where a tourist boom
provides what could be the best hope for saving this endangered
spot in southern Mexico. ``We've made the decision to protect this
place, so that it will still be here for our children and their
children,'' says peasant farmer turned environmentalist, Francisco
Ambrocia Martinez. (Jim Langdon/Houston Chronicle Photo)
