MEXICO-BUTTERFLIES-1-HNS, 03-01 -- Doug Locke of Rochester Hills,
Michigan, takes pictures of monarch butterflies near Angangueo,
Mexico. As the winter home of the vast majority of monarch
butterflies, many environmentalists and scientists, see this area
as one of the world's most endangered. During the last two years,
the number of monarchs wintering here has diminished by 70 percent.
(Jim Langdon/Houston Chronicle Photo) *LITE
