   EXCLUSIVE-URANIUM-WASTE _ The Energy Department plans to
announce this week that it wants to build two plants, at a cost of
nearly $200 million each, that will gradually turn 1.5 billion
pounds of depleted uranium into marketable products or waste that
can be safely stored. By Matthew L. Wald.
